column15:
S/N:DAJ01-C7926
Work Scope:
_x000D_ 1. Identify compressor blades to be removed and replaced. Ensure new blades are provided by customer, otherwise contact ethos energy lit to request new blades to be used.
_x000D_ 2. Setup disc onto suitable table and prepare to remove compressor blades. Use a brass drift and a hammer to remove each blade from disc. Hit the face of the blade root to break the interference fit and to slide the blade out of the disc.
_x000D_ 3. Clean compressor blade serrations from disc and strip clean traces of old coating. Chemical clean with alkaline products similar to "cee-bee cleaner j84" is acceptable. If required, mask all uncoated surfaces to prepare for grit blasting of previously coated surfaces in order to remove all coating traces fully. Avoid any damage on critical areas resulting from grit blast. Blow off part to remove any traces of grit blast material. Wash& rinse part as needed.
_x000D_ 4. Perform non-destructive test: fluorescent liquid penetrant inspection (NDT-FPI) per ASTM e1417. Provide written report documenting findings from NDT inspection. Test and report to be conducted by a certified level 2 NDT inspector. If no valid indications are observed during NDT then "accept" part in the report, otherwise "reject" part and notify ethos energy about condition observed for further evaluation and disposition providing test final report showing relevant indications, location, size and quantity -according with ASTM standard.
_x000D_ 5. Install new blades into compressor disc slots. Adjust the axial position of each blade so that all airfoils are leveled to each other. Secure all blades in place with a lock using a round punch drift and a hammer.
_x000D_ 6. Provide NDT report and contact Ethos Energy QC Department with any question

_x000D_ General PO notes:
_x000D_ Post machining apply Alseal 625
_x000D_ Final thickness 25-75 microns
_x000D_ Spray Part, Curing is performed immediately after removal from the spray booth in_x000D_ an oven at 340C (645F) this is just a drying sequence that prevents the paint from_x000D_ re-wetting before being placed in the furnace.

_x000D_ Difusion vacuum heat treatment to be performed at 1650 F / 900C for 2 hours.
_x000D_ Coated parts should then be allowed to `bisque in a high humidity (80%) room with extraction for around 12 hours and glass beaded to remove the bisque
_x000D_ for 1st stage 2pcs @ 0.080 and 2pcs @ 0.060
_x000D_ for 2nd stage 2pcs @ 0.080 and 2pcs@ 0.060
_x000D_
_x000D_ Perform metallographic examination of coating
_x000D_ Evaluate & report per AVO 08 revision 2:12 acceptance criteria.
_x000D_ Keep sets separated
